article.headline: Colorado State 91, Texas Southern 66
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Matt Nelson had 17 points and Jon Rakiecki added a season-high 13 to lead Colorado State to a 91-66 victory over Texas Southern on Thursday night. Nelson was 5-for-6 shooting and 7-for-8 from the free-throw line despite getting just 19 minutes of playing time because of foul trouble. Rakiecki was 4-for-6 on 3-pointers. Colorado State (3-2) hit 25-of-35 free throws. Michael Sneed had 16 points and seven rebounds for Texas Southern (1-3). The Tigers shot just 30 percent in the second half. Colorado State held the Tigers without a field goal for four minutes while going on a 13-3 run in the second half. Nelson and Matt Williams had five points each after a jumper by Allan Lovett with 15:50 remaining. Williams converted a missed shot into a rebound basket to give Colorado State a 78-58 lead. Williams, who had all 12 of his points in the second half, accounted for seven of the Rams' final 15 points. Texas Southern trailed 47-38 at halftime but had been as close as 39-38 after a free throw by Sneed with 1:31 left in the first. Dwight Boatner ignited an 8-0 run with four points off two steals in the final minute of the half for Colorado State.
